data.text:
2020-21: Season canceled due to COVID-19.

2019-20: Named to the NIRA All-Academic Team ... Helped the Bears reach the NIRA 15s Championship match … Recorded a try at Queens … Registered a try and led the Bears defensively at Sacred Heart … Logged two tries at AIC and West Chester … Captain for 7s.

2018-19: Captain ... Selected to the Ivy Rugby Conference 7s Team ... Helped the team qualify for the NIRA Quarterfinals in 15s ... Recorded a try against West Chester (Sept. 22) and Norwich (Oct. 28) ... Registered two tries against West Chester (April 6) to help the Bears finish third at Brown 7s.

2017-18: Member of the team that captured the Ivy Championship in 15s with a 62-25 win over Princeton (Oct. 28) ... Helped the squad win the Plate Division at Crimson 7s ... Member of the team that reached the championship match at Pioneer 7s.

Before Brown: Competed in field hockey, volleyball and rugby 7s at Ashbury College ... Recipient of the Roy Napier Cup, awarded to the student who best exemplifies the spirit of sport at Ashbury ... Most Valuable Player for field hockey, volleyball and rugby teams ... Named Most Improved Player in 2016 for field hockey, volleyball and rugby ... Also competed for the New York 7s, winning the Premier Division Championship, and the Las Vegas 7s ... School captain in 2016-17.

Personal: Born December 31, 1999 ... Daughter of Carol and Don Wang ... Has one sibling, Kyler ... Concentrating in Biology.
